b'' b'' b'my syllogism is of the form:' b'a is b.' b'c is a.' b'therefore c is b.' b'' b'this is a logically valid construction.' b'' b'your syllogism, however, is of the form:' b'a is b.' b'c is b.' b'therefore c is a.' b'' b'therefore yours is a logically invalid construction,' b"and your comments don't apply." b'' b'i appeal to mathew (mantis) here who wrote the excellent' b'post (now part of the faq) on logical argument.' b'' b'jim b.' b'' b'i am not mathew (mantis) but any (successful) first year logic student will see that you are logically correct, the other poster is logically incorrect.' b'' b'--' b'"i know" is nothing more than "i believe" with pretentions.' 